                <h3>Give the gift of literacy and intercultural understanding</h3>
                <p>We're passionate about worldwide literacy and giving a voice to people who speak minority languages. What's the point of enabling awesome presentations if most people in the world can't enjoy it? What's the point if we only help people who are already resource rich and fail to give a voice to those who can only express themselves in their native language?</p>
                <p>SPF is designed to do both of these things. We make it easy for you to get your content into many langauges and share it widely. We also make it possible for people from other languages to create and share their content in many languages. Here is how it works.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="4u">
                <p>When you use SPF and submit translated content, this information is collected and used to improve a machine translation system. The more data the system has, the better it performs so that translations become easier and cheaper to produce the more content you add.</p>
                <p>Secondly, when you financially support SPF by giving or paying for plan, a portion of the funds is set aside to subsidize the cost of the platform for people all around the world. As they create more content, they also improve the machine translation system for their languages.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="4u">
                <p>At the heart of all of this is of course great content. It doesn't matter what language is used, when there is great content, people want it--language is just one thing that prevents them from enjoying it.</p>
                <p>We believe that by making it easy to produce, share, and enjoy multilingual content from in-person experiences, we will give a voice to those who have none, advance worldwide literacy, and help people simply get to know each other and understand each other from their unique cultural experiences.</p>
